 to changes in the eccentricity and the longitude of perihelion and sensitive only to changes in the obliquity of the earth. For past orbital changes, both the seasonal and the mean annual model fail to produce glacial advances of the magnitude that are thought to have occurred.{$<$}/p{$><$}/section{$>$}},
